## ğŸ“‹ **StyleSheet API**

The `StyleSheet` API provides a way to create and manage styles in React Native.

### **Basic StyleSheet Usage**

<button onclick="copyCode(this)" class="copy-btn">ğŸ“‹ Copy</button>
{% raw %}
```javascript
import React from 'react';
import { View, Text, StyleSheet } from 'react-native';

const BasicStyling = () => {
  return (
    <View style={styles.container}>
      <Text style={styles.title}>Welcome to React Native</Text>
      <Text style={styles.subtitle}>Styling with StyleSheet</Text>
      <View style={styles.card}>
        <Text style={styles.cardText}>This is a card component</Text>
      </View>
    </View>
  );
};

const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  container: {
    flex: 1,
    backgroundColor: '#f5f5f5',
    padding: 20,
  },
  title: {
    fontSize: 24,
    fontWeight: 'bold',
    color: '#333',
    marginBottom: 10,
    textAlign: 'center',
  },
  subtitle: {
    fontSize: 16,
    color: '#666',
    marginBottom: 20,
    textAlign: 'center',
  },
  card: {
    backgroundColor: 'white',
    padding: 20,
    borderRadius: 10,
    shadowColor: '#000',
    shadowOffset: {
      width: 0,
      height: 2,
    },
    shadowOpacity: 0.25,
    shadowRadius: 3.84,
    elevation: 5,
  },
  cardText: {
    fontSize: 16,
    color: '#444',
    lineHeight: 24,
  },
});

export default BasicStyling;
```
